# Electron and `shared/`

## Import boundaries

- **`shared/**`**: Domain logic, validation, and timer behavior shared by the Nuxt app and Electron. Keep it free of Nuxt/Vue and free of direct `electron` imports so the same modules stay usable in the browser build.
- **`electron/**`**: Main process, preload, tray, and desktop IPC. May import from `shared/**`and other`electron/**`modules. Do **not** import from`app/`(the renderer is the Nuxt build, not source under`app/`).
- **`app/**`**: Nuxt UI and Firestore. May import from `shared/**`. Do **not** import from `electron/**` (Electron APIs are not available in the web target).

Reuse **`shared/worklog`** for timer and validation logic instead of duplicating it across app and Electron.

## When to run `npm run electron:build`

Run it when changing **desktop** behavior or packaging: Electron main/preload, IPC contracts, tray/window/audio integration, or Electron-related build config. It is heavier than `npm run build`; use the web build alone when you only touch the Nuxt app.

Also run **`npm run typecheck:electron`** (or full `npm run check` / `npm run verify`) when editing `electron/**` or `shared/**`, since those paths are covered by `tsconfig.electron.json`.
